  "body": "This is [already tested at the unit test level](https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/4875ba3a64d9a438c452e5c855a6fe2f83d5f5d8/consensus/merge/src/test/java/org/hyperledger/besu/consensus/merge/MergeProtocolScheduleTest.java#L58-L82) and we should first check if this type of test is already present in Hive.\n\nIf not, then an Acceptance Test for ensuring shanghai EVM changes are enabled when shanghai is enabled would be useful. The context is that MergeProtocolSchedule.applyMergeSpecificModifications has now been responsible twice for causing a bug where the shanghai (or subsequent forks) configuration is reverted back to paris. For Shanghai, this only has impact on the EVM configuration.\n\nOne way to do this would be to send a transaction containing a PUSH0.\n",
